In addition to the fan, the client wanted to update the main lighting fixture in the kitchen. She didn't like the look of any of the pre-made fixtures she found, so we customized this one to suit her needs. It blend seamlessly with the fan to provide a much needed update to the room's feel.
Our Latest Projects

In addition to the fan, the client wanted to update the main lighting fixture in the kitchen. She didn't like the look of any of the pre-made fixtures she found, so we customized this one to suit her needs. It blend seamlessly with the fan to provide a much needed update to the room's feel.

The client wanted a custom coffee table to accessorize their guest suite. They wanted something with a pop of color, so we designed and built this all-wood coffee table for them. The top is made out of beautiful purpleheart wood. The addition of curly maple legs lightens the piece without distracting from the incredible natural color of the purpleheart.

The client gave us full creative control of this one. She wanted a unique coffee table to furnish her living room and couldn't find anything she liked. We finished this incredible live-edge slab of Monkeypod wood with nothing but a coat of high gloss resin to retain the natural beauty of the wood and protect it from everyday messes.

The client wanted to update their kitchen/dining space with a more modern and functional lighting piece. We felt the lack of air movement in the space called for a fan and together with the client, chose this unique piece.
